scanner /ˈskænə/

(scanners) 

1. N-COUNT A scanner is a machine which is used to examine, identify, or record things, for example by using a beam of light, sound, or X-rays. 扫描设备 

例： ...brain scanners. …大脑扫描仪。 

2. N-COUNT A scanner is a piece of computer equipment that you use for copying a picture or document into a computer. 扫描仪 [计算机] 

例： ...a colour printer and scanner. …一台彩色打印机和扫描仪。

